
@startuml

class Student {
  + String studentID
  + String name
  + List<Course> coursesRegistered
  + requestAppointment(course: Course, date: Date, time: Time)
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  + String taID
  + String name
  + List<Course> coursesTaught
  + acceptAppointment(appointment: Appointment)
}

class Course {
  + String courseId
  + String courseName
  + List<Student> studentsRegistered
  + List<TeachingAssistant> teachingAssistants
}

class Appointment {
  + String appointmentID
  + Date date
  + Time time
  + Course course
  + TeachingAssistant assistant
  + Student student
  + boolean isConfirmed
}

Student "1" -- "0..*" Course : registeredFor
Course "1" -- "1..*" TeachingAssistant : hasTA
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : handles
Student "1" -- "1" Appointment : requests
Course "1" -- "1" Appointment : relatesTo
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "1" Appointment : provides

@enduml

### Explanation of Associations:
- **Student** can be registered for multiple **Courses**.
- A **Course** has one or more **Teaching Assistants** who are assigned to teach it.
- A **Teaching Assistant** can handle multiple **Appointments**.
- A **Student** can request an **Appointment** for a specific **Course**.
- An **Appointment** is linked to exactly one **Course**, one **Teaching Assistant**, and one **Student**.
- Constraints are implied by the associations (e.g., only registered students can request appointments for their registered courses, TAs can only assist in courses they are assigned to).

